description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;0-19 Universal Service Manager Luton&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band - 8a&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full-time, 37.5hrs per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanant&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Based in Luton&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Luton is a super diverse densely populated town where 37% of the children live in poverty. Are you an experienced motivated senior Public Health Nurse who would like to lead a team which is committed to improving the outcomes for Luton’s children? If so this is the Job you for you. You will be leading a team of dedicated staff who have chosen Luton as a place where their work can make a real difference. The post holder will be working with colleagues across the system including our council colleagues who are constantly innovating to improve the experience of childhood here. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The portfolio includes all of 0-19 services, Health Visiting, School Nursing, Children Looked After and Youth offending. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for someone who has&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A passion for improving outcomes for Children and families&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working across organisational boundaries developing a common purpose approach to improvements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to engage with teams both internally and externally&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven ability in operational management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambridgeshire Community Services is an organisation which receives excellent staff feedback from the annual NHS Staff Satisfaction Survey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cambridgeshire Community Services, the health and wellbeing of our staff is our priority; our embedded philosophy is Live Life Well as we strive to ensure a healthy, safe and happy workplace.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closure date 9.11.2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date 18.11.2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like more information on this role or to have an informal discussion, please contact Tina Charlton on 07813128449 or email tina.charlton4@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
